foia:ProcessedConsultationSection.foia:FootnoteText: Historically, DoD did not tracked “consultations” separately from FOIA requests. The Department of Justice directed agencies to track and report on consultations separately beginning July 1, 2008, if feasible. On that date, some DoD components were able to retroactively determine which of their open FOIA requests were “consultations;” however, most did not. At the end of FY 08, some components still were not able to configure their data tracking systems to account for consultations. All components are now tracking consultations separately.
